 class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 03, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bbu1665702692717.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bbu1665702692717.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bbu1665702692717.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bbu1665702692717\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"bbu1665702692717__uinstopn_405086\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Get a handle to an existing component instance.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"bbu1665702692717__topic_d121547e1_d121548e1_d121549e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104bbu1665702692717_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"bbu1665702692717__codeblock_qwq_mtc_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">long uinstopn (UHACT hEnv, UCHAR* instName, UHACT* phInst);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bbu1665702692717__topic_d86217e1_d86218e1_d86219e1_d86220e1_d86221e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d998325e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"bbu1665702692717__parml_zmr_ntc_bwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">hEnv</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The environment handle as returned by <code class=\"ph codeph\">uecreate</code> or\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">ueopen</code></dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">instName</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The name of the existing instance of which we want the handle</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">phInst</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">(Output) The instance handle</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bbu1665702692717__topic_d86222e1_d86223e1_d86224e1_d86225e1_d86226e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d998325e105\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bbu1665702692717__d6412e20\">See the \"Call-In API Return Codes\" topic. </p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bbu1665702692717__topic_d86227e1_d86228e1_d86229e1_d86230e1_d86231e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d998325e114\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bbu1665702692717__d5956e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">ucall</span></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bbu1665702692717__topic_d86232e1_d86233e1_d86234e1_d86235e1_d86236e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d998325e126\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bbu1665702692717__p_d121571e1_d121572e1_d121573e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uinstopn</code> can be used to get a\n            handle to an existing instance.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bbu1665702692717__p_d121574e1_d121575e1_d121576e1\">In Uniface V7, every instance could be uniquely identified by its name. So it was always possible to use <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinstopn</code> to get a handle to any instance. However, since then, instance names are no longer globally unique. For example, the instance name on the client might or might not match the instance name on the server. So it is not always possible to know the real name of a given instance.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"bbu1665702692717__note_N10091_N10078_N10016_N10001\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Therefore, <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinstopn</code> is deprecated. If you need a handle\n            to an existing instance, have the 4GL pass this handle to your 3GL code as a\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">handle</code> parameter. You can then directly use that handle to activate\n            operations in that instance.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jhh1665702691902.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Call-In API Return Codes</a><p>Codes that can possibly be returned by functions from the 3GL call-in API are consistent with the values returned by the ProcScript function $procerror, unless noted otherwise.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vni1707830115353.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Handles</a><p>A handle is a reference to an object, such as a synchronous component instance, entity, occurrence, or field. Handles can be used to call operations on the referenced object, or to pass these objects as variables and parameters.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iou1665702692361.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uinstnew</a><p>Create a new instance of a Uniface 4GL component.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525964\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525964\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uinstopn Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 03, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Get a handle to an existing component instance. Explain this code long uinstopn (UHACT hEnv, UCHAR* instName, UHACT* phInst); Copy Parameters hEnv The environment handle as returned by uecreate or ueopen instName The name of the existing instance of which we want the handle phInst (Output) The instance handle Return Values See the \"Call-In API Return Codes\" topic. Use Library: ucall Description uinstopn can be used to get a handle to an existing instance. In Uniface V7, every instance could be uniquely identified by its name. So it was always possible to use uinstopn to get a handle to any instance. However, since then, instance names are no longer globally unique. For example, the instance name on the client might or might not match the instance name on the server. So it is not always possible to know the real name of a given instance. Note: Therefore, uinstopn is deprecated. If you need a handle to an existing instance, have the 4GL pass this handle to your 3GL code as a handle parameter. You can then directly use that handle to activate operations in that instance. Related Links Call-In API Return Codes Codes that can possibly be returned by functions from the 3GL call-in API are consistent with the values returned by the ProcScript function $procerror, unless noted otherwise. Handles A handle is a reference to an object, such as a synchronous component instance, entity, occurrence, or field. Handles can be used to call operations on the referenced object, or to pass these objects as variables and parameters. uinstnew Create a new instance of a Uniface 4GL component. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}